<s snum=66>Now, if this were Vivian next door to him and if, for some obscure female reason, she kept her clothes in the refrigerator, they would not be pink.</s>
<s snum=67>They would be black or white or horse-blanket plaid, chic and splashy, like Vivian herself.</s>
<s snum=68>Pink, Vivian once had told him, was for baby girls, and grown-up girls who wore pink were subconsciously clinging to their infancy.</s>
