<s snum=135>At two that morning, he was still walking- up and down Peony, up and down the veranda, up and down the silent, moonlit beach.</s>
<s snum=136>Finally, in desperation, he opened the refrigerator, filched her hand lotion, and left a note.</s>
<s snum=137>``I've got this sunburn'', said the note, ``and I used some of your hand lotion.</s>
<s snum=138>Hope you don't mind''.</s>
