<p>
<s snum=142>This was a very warm, sympathetic girl, he decided.</s>
<s snum=143>Sympathy is a fine quality in a woman.</s>
<s snum=144>Now Vivian, for instance, was not too long on sympathy.</s>
<s snum=145>She felt, and said, that sympathy only made people feel sorry for themselves; it was a tough world, and you had to be tough to hold your own.</s>
